Sección 1.11-4 Numerical Integration and Estimating Signal Energy
x3 = @(t2) exp(-t2).*((t2>=0)&(t2<1));
t2 = (0:0.01:1);
E_x1 = sum(x3(t2).*x3(t2)*0.01)
E_x1 = 0.4367
x1_squared = @(t2) x3(t2).*x3(t2);
E_x1 = quad(x1_squared,0,1)
E_x1 = 0.4323
g_squared = @(t2) g(t2).*g(t2);
t2 = (0:0.001:100);
E_g = sum(g_squared(t2)*0.001)
E_g = 0.2567
E_g = quad(g_squared,0,100)
E_g = 0.2562

Problema 3

1.11-1 Provide MATLAB code and output that plots the odd portion (t) of the function over a suitable-length interval using a suitable number of points.
unit = @(t) 1.0.*(t>=0);
fun = @(t) (2.^-t).*cos(2*pi*t);
t = (0:0.01:10);
Sol = fun(t).*unit(t-pi);
subplot(3,1,1),plot(t,Sol,'color','r'),title('x(t) Original');
xlabel('t'); ylabel('x(t)');
grid on; hold on;
t = (0:0.01:10);
Res = (fun(t).*unit(t-pi)-(fun(-t).*unit(-t-pi)))/2;
subplot(3,1,2),plot(t,Res,'color','b'),title('x(t) impar');
xlabel('t'); ylabel('-x(-t)');
grid on; hold on;
subplot(3,1,3),plot(t,Res);,title('Original vs impar');
hold on
subplot(3,1,3),plot(t,Sol);
legend('impar','Original');
set(gcf,'color','y');
xlabel('t'); ylabel('-x(-t)');
grid on; hold on;

Problema 5

(e) gráfica de x(t) para
a)
u=@(t) 1.0.*(t>=0);
x=@(t) exp(t*(1+1j*2*pi)).*u(-t);
y=@(t) real(2*x((-5-t)/2));
t=linspace(-10,10,500);
figure
plot3(t,imag(x(0.5*t)),real(x(t)),'r');
title('Grafica inciso a');
xlabel('t');
ylabel('Imag');
zlabel('Real');
grid on;
hold on;
plot3(t,imag(x(1*t)),real(x(t)),'g');
plot3(t,imag(x(2*t)),real(x(t)),'b');
legend('escalar=0.5','escalar=1','escalar=2');
hold off;
El factor escal a es importante ya que cambia la amplitud y periodo de la señal como podemos ver en la grafica.
b)
figure
plot(t,y(t),'g')
title('Grafica inciso b');
xlabel('t');
ylabel('y(t)');
grid on;
Vemos que la señal de un salto en t=-5
